  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Looking for an Operations Manager specialize in Electrical",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking an experienced <strong>Operations Manager (Electrical)</strong> to oversee and manage electrical projects and daily operations. The candidate will be responsible for ensuring projects are delivered on time, within budget, and in compliance with quality and safety standards.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Manage and oversee electrical operations and project execution</p></li><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and monitor site activities and manpower</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with safety regulations, codes, and standards</p></li><li><p>Liaise with clients, consultants, suppliers, and subcontractors</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, cost control, and resource allocation</p></li><li><p>Resolve site issues and provide technical guidance to teams</p></li><li><p>Prepare reports, schedules, and operational documentation</p></li><li><p>Ensure quality workmanship and timely completion of works</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Degree/Diploma in Electrical Engineering or related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum 7<strong>–9 years</strong> relevant experience in electrical/M&E operations</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of electrical systems, codes, and site practices</p></li><li><p>Proven leadership and team management skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously</p></li><li><p>Good communication and problem-solving skills</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Experience in M&E or construction industry especially in LTA projects</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with safety and quality management systems</p></li><li><p>Experience handling large-scale electrical projects including LTA projects</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Benefits:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Competitive salary</p></li><li><p>Career growth opportunities</p></li><li><p>Supportive and professional work environment</p></li></ul>",
